- "big spenders" refers to customers with high total spending; 
- "splurged the most" means having the highest total spent; 
- "latest sales drive" refers to a specific campaign (campaign ID = 1 in this case).

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT order_id) AS unique_orders
FROM page_visits
WHERE pages_visited > 10;

SELECT colour
FROM tshirt_inventory
WHERE stock_quantity < low_stock_threshold;

SELECT customer_id
FROM customers
ORDER BY total_spent DESC;
